SPICY GUACAMOLE raced up close in the five path, lost ground under a drive in the three path rounding the turn, tipped out to the four path into the stretch, and ran on for show. LLAMARADA was behind in the seven path going into the turn, was driven form the five path into the stretch, but made no impact. MIGUEL'S BELLE had a slow start, chased in the five path, floated out to the seven path into the lane, and did not threaten. KAITIE KAIT bumped with an outer foe at the start, prompted the early pace inside, but had to check passing the half, and failed to menace.
